NZBGet is a binary downloader, which downloads files from Usenet
based on information given in nzb-files. NZBGet is written in C++
and is known for its extraordinary performance and efficiency.

NZBGet either needs a configuration file or options passed on the
command-line. There is a default configuration template located at
/usr/share/nzbget/nzbget.conf. Copy and edit this file. By default,
NZBGet looks for this file in:
  * <app-directory>/nzbget.conf
  * ~/.nzbget
  * /etc/nzbget.conf
  * /usr/etc/nzbget.conf
  * /usr/local/etc/nzbget.conf
  * /opt/etc/nzbget.conf

NZBGet can be run as a daemon. There is a sample init located at
/usr/share/nzbget/rc.nzbget you can edit and use. One option to use
NZBGet as a daemon would be to do the following as root:

    # groupadd nzbget
    # useradd -d /var/lib/nzbget -s /bin/false -g nzbget nzbget
    
    # cp -a /usr/share/nzbget/rc.nzbget /etc/rc.d/nzbget/rc.nzbget
    # chmod +x /etc/rc.d/nzbget/rc.nzbget
    
    # mkdir -p /var/lib/nzbget
    # cp -a /usr/share/nzbget/nzbget.conf /var/lib/nzbget/nzbget.conf
    # chown -R nzbget:nzbget /var/lib/nzbget
